defs.docs: Cranelift IR builder library.

defs.name: FunctionBuilderContext
defs.docs: Structure used for translating a series of functions into Cranelift IR.

defs.name: FunctionBuilder
defs.docs: Temporary object used to build a single Cranelift IR `Function`.

defs.name: func
defs.docs:
The function currently being built.
 This field is public so the function can be re-borrowed.

defs.name: Position
defs.docs: Position

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Creates a FunctionBuilderContext structure. The structure is automatically cleared after
 each [`FunctionBuilder`](struct.FunctionBuilder.html) completes translating a function.

defs.name: FuncInstBuilder
defs.docs:
Implementation of the [`InstBuilder`](cranelift_codegen::ir::InstBuilder) that has
 one convenience method per Cranelift IR instruction.

defs.name: new
defs.value: fn (func: &'a mut Function, func_ctx: &'a mut FunctionBuilderContext, position: &'a mut Position) -> Self
defs.docs:
Creates a new FunctionBuilder structure that will operate on a `Function` using a
 `FunctionBuilderContext`.

defs.name: set_srcloc
defs.docs: Set the source location that should be assigned to all new instructions.

defs.name: create_ebb
defs.docs: Creates a new `Ebb` and returns its reference.

defs.name: switch_to_block
defs.docs:
After the call to this function, new instructions will be inserted into the designated
 block, in the order they are declared. You must declare the types of the Ebb arguments
 you will use here.

defs.name: seal_block
defs.docs: Declares that all the predecessors of this block are known.

defs.name: seal_all_blocks
defs.docs: Effectively calls seal_block on all blocks in the function.

defs.name: declare_var
defs.value: fn (&mut self, var: Variable, ty: Type) -> ()
defs.docs: In order to use a variable in a `use_var`, you need to declare its type with this method.

defs.name: use_var
defs.docs:
Returns the Cranelift IR value corresponding to the utilization at the current program
 position of a previously defined user variable.

defs.name: def_var
defs.value: fn (&mut self, var: Variable, val: Value) -> ()
defs.docs:
Register a new definition of a user variable. The type of the value must be
 the same as the type registered for the variable.

defs.name: set_val_label
defs.value: fn (&mut self, val: Value, label: ValueLabel) -> ()
defs.docs: Set label for Value

defs.name: create_jump_table
defs.docs: Creates a jump table in the function, to be used by `br_table` instructions.

defs.name: create_stack_slot
defs.docs:
Creates a stack slot in the function, to be used by `stack_load`, `stack_store` and
 `stack_addr` instructions.

defs.name: import_signature
defs.docs: Adds a signature which can later be used to declare an external function import.

defs.name: import_function
defs.docs: Declare an external function import.

defs.name: create_global_value
defs.docs: Declares a global value accessible to the function.

defs.name: create_heap
defs.docs: Declares a heap accessible to the function.

defs.name: ins
defs.docs:
Returns an object with the [`InstBuilder`](cranelift_codegen::ir::InstBuilder)
 trait that allows to conveniently append an instruction to the current `Ebb` being built.

defs.name: ensure_inserted_ebb
defs.docs: Make sure that the current EBB is inserted in the layout.

defs.name: cursor
defs.docs: Returns a `FuncCursor` pointed at the current position ready for inserting instructions.

defs.name: append_ebb_params_for_function_params
defs.docs:
Append parameters to the given `Ebb` corresponding to the function
 parameters. This can be used to set up the ebb parameters for the
 entry block.

defs.name: append_ebb_params_for_function_returns
defs.docs:
Append parameters to the given `Ebb` corresponding to the function
 return values. This can be used to set up the ebb parameters for a
 function exit block.

defs.name: finalize
defs.docs:
Declare that translation of the current function is complete. This
 resets the state of the `FunctionBuilder` in preparation to be used
 for another function.

defs.name: ebb_params
defs.docs:
Retrieves all the parameters for an `Ebb` currently inferred from the jump instructions
 inserted that target it and the SSA construction.

defs.name: signature
defs.docs: Retrieves the signature with reference `sigref` previously added with `import_signature`.

defs.name: append_ebb_param
defs.value: fn (&mut self, ebb: Ebb, ty: Type) -> Value
defs.docs:
Creates a parameter for a specific `Ebb` by appending it to the list of already existing
 parameters.

defs.name: inst_results
defs.docs: Returns the result values of an instruction.

defs.name: change_jump_destination
defs.value: fn (&mut self, inst: Inst, new_dest: Ebb) -> ()
defs.docs: Changes the destination of a jump instruction after creation.

defs.name: is_unreachable
defs.docs: Returns `true` if and only if the current `Ebb` is sealed and has no predecessors declared.

defs.name: is_pristine
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if and only if no instructions have been added since the last call to
 `switch_to_block`.

defs.name: is_filled
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if and only if a terminator instruction has been inserted since the
 last call to `switch_to_block`.

defs.name: display
defs.value: fn <'b, I> (&'b self, isa: I) -> DisplayFunction
defs.docs: Returns a displayable object for the function as it is.

defs.name: call_memcpy
defs.value: fn (&mut self, config: TargetFrontendConfig, dest: Value, src: Value, size: Value) -> ()
defs.docs: Calls libc.memcpy

defs.name: emit_small_memcpy
defs.value: fn (&mut self, config: TargetFrontendConfig, dest: Value, src: Value, size: u64, dest_align: u8, src_align: u8) -> ()
defs.docs: Optimised memcpy for small copies.

defs.name: call_memset
defs.value: fn (&mut self, config: TargetFrontendConfig, buffer: Value, ch: Value, size: Value) -> ()
defs.docs: Calls libc.memset

defs.name: emit_small_memset
defs.value: fn (&mut self, config: TargetFrontendConfig, buffer: Value, ch: u8, size: u64, buffer_align: u8) -> ()
defs.docs: Calls libc.memset

defs.name: call_memmove
defs.value: fn (&mut self, config: TargetFrontendConfig, dest: Value, source: Value, size: Value) -> ()
defs.docs: Calls libc.memmove

defs.name: emit_small_memmove
defs.value: fn (&mut self, config: TargetFrontendConfig, dest: Value, src: Value, size: u64, dest_align: u8, src_align: u8) -> ()
defs.docs: Optimised memmove for small moves.

defs.name: Block
defs.docs: A opaque reference to a basic block.

defs.name: Switch
defs.docs:
Unlike with `br_table`, `Switch` cases may be sparse or non-0-based.
 They emit efficient code using branches, jump tables, or a combination of both.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new empty switch

defs.name: set_entry
defs.value: fn (&mut self, index: EntryIndex, ebb: Ebb) -> ()
defs.docs: Set a switch entry

defs.name: emit
defs.value: fn (self, bx: &mut FunctionBuilder, val: Value, otherwise: Ebb) -> ()
defs.docs: Build the switch

defs.name: Variable
defs.docs: An opaque reference to a variable.

defs.name: with_u32
defs.docs: Create a new Variable with the given index.

defs.name: VERSION
defs.docs: Version number of this crate.
